  "prompt": "What is the most embarrassing punishment in Indian schools?",
  "response": "In Indian schools, some forms of punishment that have been considered embarrassing or humiliating include:\n\n1. **Physical Punishments**: While now illegal, practices like caning or slapping were previously common and can be deeply embarrassing for students.\n  \n2. **Public Shaming**: Students may be made to stand in front of the class, wear a sign, or write on the board about their mistakes, which can be humiliating.\n\n3. **Humiliation in Front of Peers**: Some teachers might call out a student for poor performance or behavior, leading to embarrassment in front of classmates.\n\n4. **Isolation**: Being made to sit separately from classmates or sent to the corner of the room can also be a form of punishment that feels embarrassing.\n\n5. **Forced Apologies**: Having to publicly apologize or write letters of apology can be humiliating for students, particularly if they feel the punishment is unjust.\n\nMany schools are moving away from these practices toward more constructive forms of discipline that focus on positive reinforcement and guidance rather than humiliation.",
